Other
<!--File:Zentralfriedhof Vienna - Boltzmann.JPG|thumb|Boltzmann's grave with the famous entropy formula--->
* Boltzmann's grave – The Boltzmann equation was originally formulated by Ludwig Boltzmann between 1872 to 1875. It relates the entropy S of an ideal gas to the quantity W, which is the number of microstates corresponding to a given macrostate. In the ideal gas limit it exactly corresponds to the proper thermodynamic entropy.
<!---
* listing
| name=Boltzmann's grave | alt= | url= | email=
| address=Zentralfriedhof, Vienna | lat=48.149444 | long=16.441111 | directions=
| phone= | tollfree= | fax= | image=Boltzmann equation.JPG
| hours= | price=
| content=The Boltzmann equation was originally formulated by Ludwig Boltzmann between 1872 to 1875. It relates the entropy S of an ideal gas to the quantity W, which is the number of microstates corresponding to a given macrostate. In the ideal gas limit it exactly corresponds to the proper thermodynamic entropy.

--->
* Schwinger's grave – The first order correction to the fine structure constant (alpha) is engraved on Julian Schwinger's headstone at the Mt Auburn Cemetery.
<!---
* listing
| name=Schwinger's grave | alt= | url= | email=
| address=Cambridge, MA | lat=42.367351 | long=-71.146369 | directions=
